Troubleshooting Tips
Elasticsearch not starting:

Check if port 9200 is already in use: sudo netstat -tlnp | grep 9200
Review logs: sudo journalctl -u elasticsearch -n 50
Ensure sufficient memory (at least 2GB RAM)
Logstash not processing logs:

Verify configuration syntax: sudo /usr/share/logstash/bin/logstash --config.test_and_exit -f /etc/logstash/conf.d/sigma-detection.conf
Check file permissions on log files
Review Logstash logs: sudo journalctl -u logstash -n 50
No alerts appearing:

Verify test logs were generated: cat /tmp/test_auth.log
Check Elasticsearch indices: curl localhost:9200/_cat/indices?v
Query alerts directly: curl localhost:9200/security-alerts-*/_search?pretty
Python scripts failing:

Install missing packages: pip3 install elasticsearch
Verify Elasticsearch connectivity: curl localhost:9200
Check Python version: python3 --version (should be 3.6+)
